BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Katsura Sunshine’s Rakugo
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260805T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260805T203000
DTSTAMP:20260721T085036Z
UID:occ-5439@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
DESCRIPTION:Japanese rakugo comic storytelling: one kneeling performer\, a
  paper fan\, a cloth\, and about an hour of stories.\n\nRakugo is Japan's 
 centuries-old art of comic storytelling. A lone performer kneels on a rais
 ed platform and plays every character in the story\, armed with nothing bu
 t a paper fan and a small cloth\, switching roles with a shift in voice an
 d a turn of the head. Katsura Sunshine finished a traditional apprenticesh
 ip under master Katsura Bunshi VI in 2011 and has performed a monthly show
  at Manhattan's New World Stages since 2019. Presented by 7 Stages\; the p
 erformance runs about an hour.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260721T084831Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://pretix.eu/rakugo/atlanta-2/4984497/
END:VEVENT
